h3. Issue Summary

Snippet API endpoint as mentioned in the [developer guide|https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/snippets/%7Bworkspace%7D/%7Bencoded_id%7D] is not giving the expected result and returning the following error -
{code:java}
There is no API hosted at this URL.\n\nFor information about our API's, please refer to the documentation at: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/"
{code}
h3. Steps to Reproduce

Call the below API endpoint -
{code:java}
/2.0/snippets/{workspace}/{encoded_id}
{code}
h3. Expected Results

The API endpoint should return the result
h3. Actual Results

The API endpoint returns the below error -
{code:java}
There is no API hosted at this URL.\n\nFor information about our API's, please refer to the documentation at: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/"
{code}
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

If you attempt to access Bitbucket cloud through an URL that has credentials (<username>@bitbucket.org:<repoSlug>.git) through other applications such as Jira, instead of allowing you to do so, Bitbucket keeps spinning forever, with the following error in the developer tools console:
 
{code}
Uncaught (in promise) TypeError: Failed to construct 'Request': Request cannot be constructed from a URL that includes credentials: /!api/internal/user/preferences/\{uuid}/workspaces-prerelease-seen/
{code}

This is a problem as, for example, when you attempt to add a repository using this URL on Jira cloud through any project > add item > repository, you would see Bitbucket will not load at all.
